The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                        NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 Ghaziabad, Dec. 18 (PTI): Police have booked 16 engineering students for obtaining scholarships of Rs 25,000 each from the social welfare department by submitting fake income certificates.          
	Police superintendent M.M. Baig said the students had filed certificates showing their families had annual incomes less than Rs 1 lakh, making them eligible for the scheme. Police will investigate the matter further.                   
	Sultanpur (PTI): A man with a criminal record umpiring a cricket match has been shot by his local rival for giving a batsman out in Bikharpur, Uttar Pradesh. Police said the umpire was critically injured and rushed to a Lucknow hospital.                   
	Colombo (PTI): Sri Lankan fishermen have saved four Indians whose boat had capsized mid-sea in a storm. Police said the Indians, fishermen aged between 25 and 35 years, were brought on Friday to the eastern port city of Trincomalee, and were admitted to hospital.                   
	 Kochi (PTI): The city observed Saturday as Bus Day with authorities asking people to rely on public transport to reduce traffic jams and pollution. Politicians and film actors travelled by city buses to encourage people to use public transport rather than cars or bikes.                   
	Srinagar (PTI): A fire has gutted most structures in a village in the Kashmir Valley. The flames broke out in a house at Tulail in Bandipore district late on Friday night and quickly spread across the village, where most houses were made of wood and mud.                   
	Ghaziabad (PTI): Two brothers have been arrested for setting their sibling on fire over a property dispute. A police officer said Suresh and Mukesh tried to burn their elder brother Raju to death. The victim was critical with 40 per cent burns while authorities sought the fourth sibling, Priti.
                                                                                                                                              
